We built and launched Dark Mode resumes at Leet Resumes:
<a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.leetresumes.com&#x2F;blog&#x2F;leet-resumes-dark-mode" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.leetresumes.com&#x2F;blog&#x2F;leet-resumes-dark-mode</a><p>It&#x27;s fun, a way to stand out, and uses the same proven resume format we&#x27;re known for.<p>Engineers may find this format particularly interesting because software development adopted dark mode decades ahead of the general user.<p>It&#x27;s worth noting that I launched Leet Resumes on Hacker News almost 2 years ago: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;news.ycombinator.com&#x2F;item?id=25678568" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;news.ycombinator.com&#x2F;item?id=25678568</a><p>The basic idea is that we write great professional resumes for free - tips appreciated.  We started in technology only and have expanded to all resumes since.<p>A post I wrote also appeared here on Hacker News &#x27;What a great technical resume can do for you&#x27;:
<a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;news.ycombinator.com&#x2F;item?id=25092880" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;news.ycombinator.com&#x2F;item?id=25092880</a><p>As I mentioned in that earlier Show HN, &quot;we believe in being transparent, open, data-driven, and helpful, so let me know what you think!&quot;
